# StillPassingTheBuck — example plaintext fallback secrets
#
# Copy this file to .env (gitignored) and fill in real values only when you
# cannot or do not want to use the system keyring on a particular machine.
#
# The scripts ALWAYS prefer the encrypted keyring (via `keyring` + your OS
# keychain / Seahorse). These .env values are only read as a fallback.
#
# Usage options for the fallback:
#   - uv run --env-file .env python scripts/your_script.py
#   - Or let python-dotenv auto-load it (if you `uv add python-dotenv`)
#   - Or source it in your shell before running
#
# Recommended: store secrets in the keyring on your daily machine:
#   keyring set stillpassingthebuck AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
#   keyring set stillpassingthebuck AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
#   keyring set stillpassingthebuck GITHUB_TOKEN
#
# Then you can run scripts normally and they will pick up the secure values.

# --- S3 / AWS (generic example; works for any AWS usage) ---
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=us-east-1

# --- Other services (examples; add whatever your scripts need) ---
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...
# ARGENTINADATOS_API_KEY=...
# SOME_OTHER_SERVICE_TOKEN=...

# You can use any name. The get_secret("NAME") helper in data_io.py will
# look for it under the "stillpassingthebuck" keyring service first,
# then as an environment variable of the same name.
